{"ANTIC":[{"def":"\"Lords of antic fame.","pos":""}],"ANTICATARRHAL":[{"def":"Efficacious against catarrh.","pos":""},{"def":"An anticatarrhal remedy.","pos":""}],"ANTICATHODE":[{"def":"The part of a vacuum tube opposite the cathode.","pos":""}],"ANTICAUSODIC":[{"def":"Same as Anticausotic.","pos":""}],"ANTICAUSOTIC":[{"def":"Good against an inflammatory fever.","pos":""},{"def":"A remedy for such a fever.","pos":""}],"ANTICHAMBER":[{"def":"See Antechamber.","pos":""}],"ANTICHLOR":[{"def":"Any substance (but especially sodium hyposulphite) used in removing the excess of chlorine left in paper pulp or stuffs after bleaching.","pos":""}],"ANTICHRIST":[{"def":"A denier or opponent of Christ.","pos":""}],"ANTICHRISTIAN":[{"def":"Opposed to the Christian religion.","pos":""},{"def":"Opposition or contrariety to the Christian religion.","pos":""}],"ANTICHRISTIANLY":[{"def":"In an antichristian manner.","pos":""}],"ANTICHRONICAL":[{"def":"Deviating from the proper order of time.","pos":""}],"ANTICHRONISM":[{"def":"Deviation from the true order of time; anachronism.","pos":""}],"ANTICHTHON":[{"def":"Inhabitants of opposite hemispheres.","pos":""}],"ANTICIPANT":[{"def":"Anticipating; expectant; -- with of.","pos":""}],"ANTICIPATE":[{"def":"To be before in doing; to do or take before another; to preclude or prevent by prior action.","pos":""},{"def":"To take up or introduce beforehand, or before the proper or normal time; to cause to occur earlier or prematurely; as, the advocate has anticipated a part of his argument.","pos":""}],"ANTICIPATION":[{"def":"The commencing of one or more tones of a chord with or during the chord preceding, forming a momentary discord.","pos":""}],"ANTICIPATIVE":[{"def":"Anticipating, or containing anticipation.","pos":""}],"ANTICIPATOR":[{"def":"One who anticipates.","pos":""}],"ANTICIPATORY":[{"def":"Forecasting; of the nature of anticipation.","pos":""}],"ANTICIVIC":[{"def":"Opposed to citizenship.","pos":""}],"ANTICIVISM":[{"def":"Opposition to the body politic of citizens.","pos":""}],"ANTICLASTIC":[{"def":"Having to opposite curvatures, that is, curved longitudinally in one direction and transversely in the opposite direction, as the surface of a saddle.","pos":""}],"ANTICLIMAX":[{"def":"A sentence in which the ideas fall, or become less important and striking, at the close; -- the opposite of climax.","pos":""},{"def":"Inclining or dipping in opposite directions.","pos":""}],"ANTICLINAL":[{"def":"The crest or line in which strata slope or dip in opposite directions.","pos":""}],"ANTICLINE":[{"def":"A structure of bedded rocks in which the beds on both sides of an axis or axial plane dip away from the axis; an anticlinal.","pos":""}],"ANTICLINORIUM":[{"def":"The upward elevation of the crust of the earth, resulting from a geanticlinal.","pos":""}],"ANTICLY":[{"def":"Oddly; grotesquely.","pos":""}],"ANTICNESS":[{"def":"The quality of being antic.","pos":""}],"ANTICOHERER":[{"def":"A device, one form of which consists of a scratched deposit of silver on glass, used in connection with the receiving apparatus for reading wireless signals.","pos":""}],"ANTICONSTITUTIONAL":[{"def":"Opposed to the constitution; unconstitutional.","pos":""}],"ANTICONTAGIOUS":[{"def":"Opposing or destroying contagion.","pos":""}],"ANTICONVULSIVE":[{"def":"Good against convulsions.","pos":""}],"ANTICOR":[{"def":"A dangerous inflammatory swelling of a horse's breast, just opposite the heart.","pos":""}],"ANTICOUS":[{"def":"Facing toward the axis of the flower, as in the introrse anthers of the water lily.","pos":""}],"ANTICYCLONE":[{"def":"A movement of the atmosphere opposite in character, as regards direction of the wind and distribution of barometric pressure, to that of a cyclone.","pos":""}]}